Task: Replace getUserMedia with CrabCamera

Summary: Complete rewrite of webcam system to use CrabCamera native plugin (V4L2/AVFoundation/DirectShow) instead of WebKit getUserMedia, which is broken on stock Linux WebKitGTK builds.

Changes:
- src-tauri/Cargo.toml: Added crabcamera v0.8 with recording feature
- src-tauri/src/lib.rs: Registered crabcamera::init() plugin
- src-tauri/capabilities/default.json: Added all 23 CrabCamera permissions
- src-tauri/build.rs: Added all CrabCamera commands for Tauri codegen
- src/hooks/useWebcam.ts: Complete rewrite using Tauri invoke for all camera ops
- src/hooks/useWebcam.test.ts: Updated 14 tests for new CrabCamera API
- src/components/WebcamRecorder.tsx: Canvas-based preview, new device selector
- src/components/WebcamRecorder.test.tsx: Updated 12 tests for new component API

Why: getUserMedia() on Linux/WebKitGTK is fundamentally broken because Ubuntu/Fedora packages are compiled without -DENABLE_MEDIA_STREAM=ON. CrabCamera bypasses the entire WebKit media stack by using native V4L2 (Linux), AVFoundation (macOS), and DirectShow (Windows).

Test Results: 50 frontend tests pass, 149 Rust tests pass
